STOCK MARKET ANALYSIS¶

We'll be analyzing stock data related to a Three Canadian Energy Companies, from Jan 1 2017 to April 21 2023. The companies are:

1) B2Gold Corp (BTO.TO)¶
2) Tamarack Valley Energy(TVE.TO)¶
3) Arbor Metals Corp (ABR.V)¶

Plotting out Moving Averages (MA) for B2GOLD. MA50 and MA200¶

In [55]:
dataBTO['MA50'] = dataBTO['Open'].rolling(50).mean()
dataBTO['MA200'] = dataBTO['Open'].rolling(200).mean()
dataBTO[['Open','MA50','MA200']].plot(label='BTO',figsize=(16,8), title = 'MOVING AVERAGES FOR B2GOLD MA50 AND MA200');

Doing the Moving Averages analysis for 50 and 200 average days (MA50, MA200), we can conclude that when the MA50 line is above the MA200 line, the price tends to rise, on the contrary, when the MA50 line is below the MA200 line, the price tends to go down. Observing the graph, we can see that the price of the stock for B2GOLD is rising.

Part 3: Basic Financial Analysis¶

Calculating Daily Returns¶

Daily Returns inform us the precentage gain or loss if we buy the stock one day and sell it the another day. This ratio is very useful in analyzing the VOLATILITY of the stock. If Daily Returns have a wide distribution, the stock is more volatile, more risky but give you more return. The formula is as follow:

$ r_t = \frac{p_t}{p_{t-1}} -1$

Box and whisker chart¶

In [60]:
box_df = pd.concat([dataBTO['returns'],dataTVE['returns'],dataABR['returns']],axis=1)
box_df.columns = ['BTO Returns',' TVE Returns','ABR Returns']
box_df.plot(kind='box',figsize=(7,8),colormap='jet')
plt.title("BOX AND WHISKER CHART FOR THE THREE STOCKS");

If we only analyze the graph, at first glance we could conclude that Arbor Metal Corp Stock is more volatile and therefore, riskier. But previously we calculated the coefficient of variation for each of the stocks, resulting in the following:

Coefficient of variation BTO = 39.76

Coeffiecient of Variations TVE = 46.62

Coefficient of Variations ABR = 14.48

We can see thet Tamarack Valley Energy has the highest value of the coefficient, being the most risky Stock, but could give you the highest Return.
